* [symbols-outline.nvim]
  Symbol outline is a plugin that allows you to see all of the symbols in a file and jump to them.

  We are just doing standard setup, but we have chosen to do this now because of the release of edgy which allows these outlines to be used in a left pane window

  #tangle
  @code lua
  {
    -- add symbols-outline
    {
      "simrat39/symbols-outline.nvim",
      cmd = "SymbolsOutline",
      keys = { { "<leader>cs", "<cmd>SymbolsOutline<cr>", desc = "Symbols Outline" } },
      opts = {},
      config = true
    },
  },
  @end
